com.crawljax.core
Class CandidateElementExtractor

java.lang.Object
  com.crawljax.core.CandidateElementExtractor

public class CandidateElementExtractor
extends Object

This class extracts candidate elements from the DOM tree, based on the tags provided by the user. Elements can also be excluded.

extract

public List<CandidateElement> extract(List<TagElement> crawlTagElements,
                                      List<TagElement> crawlExcludeTagElements,
                                      boolean clickOnce,
                                      StateVertix currentState)
                               throws CrawljaxException
This method extracts candidate elements from the current DOM tree in the browser, based on the crawl tags defined by the user.

Parameters:
crawlTagElements - a list of TagElements to include.
crawlExcludeTagElements - a list of TagElements to exclude.
clickOnce - true if each candidate elements should be included only once.
currentState - the state in which this extract method is requested.
Returns:
a list of candidate elements that are not excluded.
Throws:
CrawljaxException - if the method fails.
